      • chooseSubtree

        protected Tree.IndexEntry chooseSubtree(Descriptor descriptor,
                                        Stack path)
        Chooses the subtree which is followed during an insertion. In duplicate mode the minIndex is evaluated to positve when with a successful search or negative when the value separator is not found, this negative value points to the position in the list where the new item should be inserted. when this position lies at the end of the list a special case is used to correct the value. In normal mode for negative values of minIndex the item must be inserted before the item at the position pointed at by the returned value. BPlusTree.Node#binarySearch(Comparable)
        Specified by:
        chooseSubtree in class Tree.Node
        Parameters:
        descriptor - the Separator of the entry which is to insert
        path - the path from the root to this Node. The default implementation does not use this path
        Returns:
        the IndexEntry pointing to the subtree which is followed during an insertion

      • redressOverflow

        protected Collection redressOverflow(Stack path,
                                     List newIndexEntries,
                                     boolean up)
        Description copied from class: Tree.Node
        Treats overflows which occur during an insertion. It splits the overflowing node in new nodes. It creates new index-entries for the new nodes. These index-entries will be be added to the given List. The method Tree.Node.post(Tree.Node.SplitInfo, Tree.IndexEntry) will be used to post the created index-entries to the parent node.
        Overrides:
        redressOverflow in class Tree.Node
        Parameters:
        path - the path from the root to the overflowing node
        newIndexEntries - a List to carry the new index-entries created by the split
        up - signals whether the top node on stack will be written into the storage by calling Tree.update(Stack path) and unfixed from the underlaying buffer by calling Tree.up(Stack path).
        Returns:
        a Collection which accrues from the given collection and the created index-entries during the split.

      • redressOverflow

        protected Tree.Node.SplitInfo redressOverflow(Stack path,
                                              Tree.Node parentNode,
                                              List newIndexEntries)
        Treats overflows which occur during an insertion. The method Tree.Node.redressOverflow(Stack, xxl.core.indexStructures.Tree.Node, List) of the super class is used to split the overflowing Node in two Nodes. It creates a new IndexEntry for the new Node. This IndexEntry will be added to the given List. Finally the new Node is linked from the split Node as BPlusTree.Node#nextNeighbor.
        Overrides:
        redressOverflow in class Tree.Node
        Parameters:
        path - the path from the root to the overflowing Node
        parentNode - the parent Node of the overflowing Node
        newIndexEntries - a List to carry the new IndexEntries created by the split
        Returns:
        a SplitInfo containing required information about the split

      • split

        protected Tree.Node.SplitInfo split(Stack path)
        Splits the overflowed node. In non duplicate mode both the leaf and index nodes are splited in the middle. In duplicate mode the leaf nodes are splited according following strategy: with leaf nodes the last element is selected and checked against the the element at 75% position, when both are equal search for further duplicates until 25% reached or no more duplicates exists, then split at found index position, otherwise split in the middle.
        Specified by:
        split in class Tree.Node
        Parameters:
        path -
        Returns:
        a SplitInfo containing all needed information about the split

      • redressUnderflow

        protected boolean redressUnderflow(Stack path)
        Treats underflows which occur during a remove operation. If the given path is empty an IllegalStateException is thrown, otherwise the method BPlusTree.Node#redressUnderflow(Stack, boolean)is called with the parameter path and true to repair the underflow.
        Parameters:
        path - the path from the root to the underflowing Node
        Returns:
        a boolean which indicates whether the parent Node was updated during the operation

      • redressUnderflow

        protected boolean redressUnderflow(Stack path,
                                   boolean up)
        Treats underflows which occur during a remove operation. In case of underflow the method (BPlusTree.IndexEntry, BPlusTree.Node, Stack, boolean) is called to repair the underflow. When the root node has only one entry the root entry pointer is deleted and replaced with the child node.
        Parameters:
        path - the path from the root to the underflowing Node
        up - signals whether the treated Nodes have to be updated in the underlying Container
        Returns:
        a boolean which indicates whether the parent Node was been updated during the operation

      • redressUnderflow

        protected boolean redressUnderflow(VariableLengthBPlusTree.IndexEntry indexEntry,
                                   VariableLengthBPlusTree.Node node,
                                   Stack path,
                                   boolean up)
        Treats underflows which occur during a remove operation. It calls the method BPlusTree.Node#merge(BPlusTree.IndexEntry, Stack)to redistribute the elements of the underflowing Node an a suitable sibling or to merge them so that the underflow is repaired.
        Parameters:
        indexEntry - the IndexEntry referring to the underflowing Node
        node - the underflowing Node
        path - the path from the root to parent of the underflowing Node
        up - signals whether the treated Nodes have to be updated in the underlying Container
        Returns:
        a boolean which indicate whether the parent Node was been updated during the operation
